Assisting in the preparation of short-term and long-term operating plans;
Examining business model and cost structure to identify areas for opportunity and business improvement;
Make vs. buy analysis for Supply Chain Optimization;
Standardizing metrics and financial system setup - Systems Development and Maintenance;
Continuous Improvement of financial processes and reporting.
Education: 4-year degree required; Accounting, Finance, Business Management or related disciplines preferred. Required Skills:      3+ years of experience in financial analysis;
Experience in a manufacturing or supply chain environment;
Must have experience in operational accounting and ability to meet operational metrics;
Strong analytical skills, desire to probe facts, identify and question assumptions, and analyze issues from different perspectives;
Working knowledge of general accounting, income statement, balance sheet, standard cost accounting, and cost systems.
